-- Earthquake of Magnitude 7.5 Strikes Kepulauan Region, USGS Website Says
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2010-10-25T15:10:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/earthquake-of-magnitude-7-5-strikes-kepulauan-region-usgs-website-says.html
A magnitude 7.5 earthquake struck
the Kepulauan Mentawai region of Indonesia, about 150 miles (240
kilometers) away from Padang, Sumatra, and 395 miles from
Singapore, the U.S. Geological Survey said on its website.  The quake was centered at a depth of 20.5 miles, according
to the USGS. A local tsunami watch is in effect, the Pacific
Tsunami Warning Center said. A “destructive widespread tsunami
threat” does not exist, according to the center.   Click here for the Related Website  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
